{"author":"Claude","data":{"alias":"barren-age-vat","assignee":"claude","description":"## Why\n\n`nava-rebar` ships as both an application and a library at v0.6.0, but there is\nno published statement of what \"0.x\" means for each surface. SemVer only\ncommunicates compatibility if consumers know which APIs are stable. Today a user\ncannot tell whether a CLI flag, a JSON-schema field, a `rebar.*` function, an\nMCP tool signature, an event format, or a config key is safe to depend on.\n\n## What\n\nAdd `docs/api-stability.md` publishing a stability matrix across every public\nsurface, and link it from the README and CONTRIBUTING:\n\n- **CLI command names/options** — stable after 1.0; deprecation before removal.\n- **`--output json` schemas** — the strongest contract; versioned, backward\n  compatible.\n- **Python `rebar.*` facade** — the documented stable subset (pairs with the\n  typed-models story); internals (`_`-prefixed) are private.\n- **MCP tool names / input+output schemas** — stable subset, deprecations\n  mirrored from the CLI.\n- **Event schema** — forward-compatible wire format, `SCHEMA_VERSION`-gated\n  (preserve-and-ignore for unknown event types).\n- **Config keys** — deprecate aliases with a documented removal window.\n\nState the pre-1.0 caveat explicitly (everything may change before 1.0 except the\nsurfaces called out as the strongest contracts).\n\n## Scope\n\nOne doc (`docs/api-stability.md`) + links from README/CONTRIBUTING. Describes\nintended policy; does not itself change any API. Reference the real mechanisms\nthat already exist (`reducer/_version.py` `SCHEMA_VERSION`, the JSON Schemas in\n`schemas/`, the `_`-private convention).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/api-stability.md` exists with a per-surface matrix covering CLI, JSON\n  schemas, Python facade, MCP tools, event schema, and config keys.\n- [ ] It names JSON output schemas + event wire format as the strongest contracts\n  and states the pre-1.0 caveat.\n- [ ] It documents the deprecation policy (deprecate-before-remove, removal\n  window) for CLI/config.\n- [ ] README and CONTRIBUTING link to it.","id":"830d-1662-c8be-45f4","parent_id":"b02d-10bc-07ee-49e7","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Publish an API-stability matrix doc across CLI/schemas/Python/MCP/events/config"},"env_id":"58e9f32e-f999-436d-9c1a-5d0eef5c9903","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783148930746552335,"uuid":"e91c6c31-cb17-465f-a0c6-0013afd9297a"}